   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM28597_1817_05_17_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">EdgeworthsTown</placeName> <date when="1817-05-17"/>May 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1817<lb/></dateline>  
               <salute>
                  My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Francis</persName>,
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>It would have given you pleasure to have<lb/>
               been present when <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH1”">Harriet</persName> brought to my<lb/>
               bed's foot this morning <hi rend = "underline">vos depêches</hi> and<lb/>
               <title ref= "./Workography.xml#Karam1">Karamania</title>. I laid aside your letter<lb/>
               and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1"> Hunters</persName> half read to examine your<lb/>
               publication. I think the book extremely <choice><orig>ele-<lb/>
               -gant</orig><reg>elegant</reg></choice>, beautifully printed and adorned<lb/>
               with engravings executed with uncommon<lb/>
               neatness and effect. We dipped into the book<lb/>
               - I like the style - And I augur well of its success,<lb/>
               With respect to your transactions<lb/>
               with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1">Hunter</persName> - nothing could be more <choice><orig>ef-<lb/>
               -fective</orig><reg>effective</reg></choice> or more ably managed. And we<lb/>
               all of us consider your account of this <choice><orig>tran-<lb/>
                saction</orig><reg>transaction</reg></choice> to be as clear and comprehensive<lb/>
               as language could permit.<lb/>
               I send you a copy of my letter to<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1">Hunter</persName> to save you some postage - But I am<lb/>
               ruining you in postage and coach-hire.<lb/></p> 
            <closer>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">R. L. E </persName>-<lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back> </back>
